't someone open a state of the art facility for tourny's in tulsa? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/boklahomasoftball.showUserPublicProfile?gid=batpimp>BatPimp</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>  Posts: 286<br> <font color=#8B0000>(5/5/03 6:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/foklahomasoftballfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=183.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: tulsa fields</span><hr size=1> Carl Smith probably has the best complex in the state for slow pitch. Nine 300' fields, scoreboards, etc.<br>
Maybe the grass could use a little work, but there isn't much more to add to it. You think Tulsa needs two facilities this size? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#C0D9D9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/boklahomasoftball.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tulsared@oklahomasoftball>Tulsa Red</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#8B0000>(5/5/03 8:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/foklahomasoftballfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=183.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: tulsa fields</span><hr size=1> I have a question ... why would Tulsa put in a state of the art facility when they hold NITs at a nice complex ... could be better, but all in all it is a good facility, and it isn't even supported by local teams?  It is ridiculous that we have a facility like Carl Smith and can't even get a 20-team tourney.  Does anyone have any insight? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/boklahomasoftball.showUserPublicProfile?gid=heritage9>Heritage 9</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#8B0000>(5/5/03 8:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/foklahomasoftballfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=183.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: tulsa fields</span><hr size=1> Your right! We only had two teams from Tulsa in the &quot;C&quot; NIT.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#C0D9D9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/boklahomasoftball.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cstring84@oklahomasoftball>cstring84</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#8B0000>(5/5/03 8:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/foklahomasoftballfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=183.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Tournament</span><hr size=1> Scheduling has alot to do w/ it.  There are usually tournaments in OKC or KC every weekend of the month.  It is difficult to schedule a tournament in T-Town when teams are going elsewhere.  Another factor is the prizes.  Why would someone want to come to Tulsa to play for a T-shirt.  If Ralph would throw a money tournament, I believe he would have plenty of teams.  Another thing is the competition!  There is only 1 maybe 2 C teams.  'Most' of the D teams around the Tulsa area are scared to play against the C teams and out of ALL the E teams, they are scared to play against the D teams.  Teams just need to suck it up and play.  I am through venting now! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/boklahomasoftball.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tulsared@oklahomasoftball>Tulsa Red</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#8B0000>(5/5/03 8:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/foklahomasoftballfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=183.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tournament</span><hr size=1> Bottom line in my opinion is it is all about promotion of the tourney.  You have to make teams WANT to play in Tulsa (including the Tulsa teams).  You have to go out and WORK to get teams in the tournaments.  As an example, Arkansas has a triple crown that has 90+ teams in EVERY leg of it.  I was really surprised that we had an Arkansas team here this weekend, because obviously the only way they heard about it was through the National USSSA website.  There was nothing posted on the Arkansas message board, the Texas message board, the Kansas message board, or the Missouri message board.  A little legwork goes a LONG way.  I can promise you that Fayetteville's complex doesn't come close to Carl Smith ... but it fills up every tourney they have.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#C0D9D9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/boklahomasoftball.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shecky@oklahomasoftball>shecky</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 58<br> <font color=#8B0000>(5/5/03 9:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/foklahomasoftballfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=183.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Thanks to Pimp.....</span><hr size=1> is why he wanted this site to take off. So that everyone in OK has access to tournaments and any information softball..... It is slowly building.. But this site still needs a lot of PR.... Spread the word.... Get it out there. Border states... Anyone who plays the great game of Softball.. Tulsa does need some big tournaments.. I'd bet if Carl Smith was to use this site. More OKC teams would turnpike it down there and pass up boomer. Boomer doesn't hold candle to Carl Smith as far as upkeep and a facility stand point...<br>
<br>
2 cents<br>
