<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/boklahomasoftball.showUserPublicProfile?gid=longball2727>longball2727</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#8B0000>(5/5/03 9:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/foklahomasoftballfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=183.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tournament</span><hr size=1> Don't hurt your arm patting yourself on the back for stepping up.<br>
Taking half the state champs from 2 years ago and adding<br>
players of the same caliber and calling yourself a D team is not really taking that much of a risk to me. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#C0D9D9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/boklahomasoftball.showUserPublicProfile?gid=heritage9>Heritage 9</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#8B0000>(5/5/03 9:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/foklahomasoftballfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=183.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Thanks to Pimp.....</span><hr size=1> Your right but Tulsa needs to make teams step up and play the better leagues and tournaments. You can't get better by beating up the little guy all the time. What I mean about that is when you play in a real competitive leagues or higher class tournaments where the competition is good then you get better, not the other way around. As a City we all need to step up or we will be left behind wondering why we can't compete at the National Level.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/boklahomasoftball.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cstring84@oklahomasoftball>cstring84</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#8B0000>(5/5/03 10:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/foklahomasoftballfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=183.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Risk....</span><hr size=1> This is a totally different team than &quot;state champs TWO years ago&quot;.  That was two years ago guy!  Alot of things have happened to that team over the past two years.  <br>
<br>
Teams have no idea how a group of guys are going to play together for the first time??  What team do you play for longball?   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#C0D9D9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/boklahomasoftball.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shecky@oklahomasoftball>shecky</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#8B0000>(5/5/03 10:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/foklahomasoftballfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=183.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Heritage9...</span><hr size=1> As I read your last post I can't help but wonder..... You sort of called other teams out to play at the level they are capable... however, in the B-ville money tournament you played in the lower division.. with all other C teams played in the upper... Now does this make sense. Have I read correctly.. Seems kind of bass ackwards to see you post a comment like that<br>
<br>
P. S. Sorry to beat a dead horse.... but.. it just don't make sense....<br>
